<a href="$CGIURL?$CGIDATA&list=$LIST&func=who&extra=$PATTERN&start=?PREVIOUS&chunksize=$CHUNKSIZE">Previous $CHUNKSIZE Addresses</a><br>
<a href="$CGIURL?$CGIDATA&list=$LIST&func=who&extra=$PATTERN&start=?NEXT&chunksize=$CHUNKSIZE">Next $CHUNKSIZE Addresses</a>

<h4 align=center>Search the Subscriber List</h4>

<ol>
  <li>Choose one of the three search methods by pressing
      the appropriate button.
  <li>Type a search pattern into the <b>Search pattern</b> box. (Please see
      the $HELP:PATTERNS help document to learn how to write
      a search pattern.
  <li>Type the number of addresses you wish to view at
      one time into the <b>Number of addresses</b> box.
  <li>Press the <b>search</b> button.
</ol>

<form method=POST action="$CGIURL">
  <input name=list type=hidden value="$LIST">
  <input name=passw type=hidden value="$PASSWORD">
  <input type=hidden name=user value="$USER">

  <input type=radio name=func value="who" checked>
  Search the $LIST subscriber list 
    (using the $HELP:WHO command)<br>
  <input type=radio name=func value="who-bounce">
  Search the $LIST subscriber list for addresses with bounces 
    (using the $HELP:WHO-bounce command)<br>
  <input type=radio name=func value="which">
  Search all of the mailing lists
    (using the $HELP:WHICH command)<br>

Search pattern: <input name=pattern value=".">
Number of addresses:
  <input name=chunksize size=6 value="$CHUNKSIZE">
  <input type=submit value="search">
</form>

<h4 align=center>Add or Remove Subscribers</h4>

<ol>
  <li>Choose one of the four add/remove methods by pressing the
      appropriate button.
  <li>Type addresses into the box, one address per line.
  <li>If addresses are being added, choose the personal settings
      for these addresses with the delivery class menu and
      setting buttons.  (See the $HELP:SET help document for more
      details on the delivery class and other settings.)
  <li>Press the <b>add or remove subscribers</b> button.
</ol>

<form method=POST action="$CGIURL">
  <input name=list type=hidden value="$LIST">
  <input name=passw type=hidden value="$PASSWORD">
  <input type=hidden name=user value="$USER">
  
  <input type=radio name=func value="subscribe-set-welcome" checked> 
  Add subscribers to the $LIST mailing list.
  Send a welcome message. <br>

  <input type=radio name=func value="subscribe-set-nowelcome"> 
  Add subscribers to the $LIST mailing list.
  <b>Do not</b> send a welcome message.<br>

  <input type=radio name=func value="unsubscribe-farewell"> 
  Remove subscribers from the $LIST mailing list.
  Send a farewell message. <br>

  <input type=radio name=func value="unsubscribe"> 
  Remove subscribers from the $LIST mailing list.
  <b>Do not</b> send a farewell message. <br>

  <textarea name=victims rows=8 cols=70>
  </textarea>

  <p>

Settings for new subscribers:
  <table>
  <tr>
    <td><small>$SETTINGS</small>
  <tr>
    <td align=center><input name=setting type=checkbox value="$SETTINGS" $SETTING_CHECKED>
  </table>

  Delivery class: 
  <select name="setting">
    <option value="$CLASSES" $CLASS_SELECTED>$CLASSES: $CLASS_DESCRIPTIONS</small>
  </select>

  <input type=submit value="add or remove subscribers">
</form>

